# RISEN â€” Template

A clean, reusable prompt framework for structured, explainable tasks.  
Fill in the YAML variables and insert your data to generate a deterministic, low-hallucination prompt.

---

## ðŸ§¾ Variables (YAML)

```yaml
role: ""
audience: ""
tone: ""
format: ""
domain_scope: ""
sources: ""
output_schema_json: |
  {
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {},
    "required": []
  }
data_block: |
  [Insert data or text to analyze here...]


<prompt>
  <!-- R: ROLE -->
  <role>
    You are a {{role}} communicating with {{audience}} using a {{tone}} tone.
  </role>

  <!-- I: INPUT -->
  <input>
    <description>Use only the following data sources.</description>
    <sources>{{sources}}</sources>
    <data>
      <![CDATA[
      {{data_block}}
      ]]>
    </data>
  </input>

  <!-- S: STEPS -->
  <steps>
    1. Read and interpret <input>.
    2. Extract key insights or patterns.
    3. Produce an output according to <expectation>.
    4. Verify that your response follows <narrowing>.
  </steps>

  <!-- E: EXPECTATION -->
  <expectation>
    <output_format>{{format}}</output_format>
    <criteria>
      - Must be factual and specific.
      - Must follow the requested format.
      - Avoid filler or generic content.
    </criteria>
    <schema><![CDATA[{{output_schema_json}}]]></schema>
  </expectation>

  <!-- N: NARROWING -->
  <narrowing>
    - Do not invent facts or speculate beyond <input>.
    - Stay within {{domain_scope}} only.
    - If uncertain, reply: "I don't have enough information."
  </narrowing>

  <!-- Optional Reflection Step -->
  <reflection>
    Review your output against <expectation>.  
    If it fails, revise once automatically.
  </reflection>
</prompt>

